column11:
  Let G be a finite group with cyclic Sylow p-subgroup, and let k be a field of
characteristic p. Then H^*(BG;k) and H_*(\Omega BG\phat;k) are A_{\infty}
algebras whose structure we determine up to quasi-isomorphism.

